comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-13T22:09:17.607Z",codex-root,"Governance extension 2026-07-13: pm-96h7 is the canonical typed relationship-graph maturity initiative under this capability. Its governance slice pm-6x7o defines semantic edge validation, profile-aware coverage, isolate waivers, counts-first audits, dry-run remediation, active-versus-terminal safety, and shared SDK findings. The all-status plan pm-a8zm is intentionally blocked until semantics and tooling exist; it forbids density-only links and separates terminal batches through pm-e9zh."
  "2026-07-18T14:08:41.384Z",codex-ecosystem-planner,"Governance baseline 2026-07-18: all active items have parent, AC, estimate, risk, confidence, and history; graph has zero actionable findings and zero active isolates. Metadata debt remains historical and already owned: validation warns validate_resolution_missing_fields:276 under pm-e9zh/pm-wenq and health warns history_unknown_author_events:5 under pm-h90s; history drift is zero. Dedupe audits found one exact/fuzzy cluster consisting solely of three already-canceled accidental probe items, and parent-scope mode found zero clusters. Do not rewrite historical terminal evidence with placeholders or manufacture graph edges. New filing pm-szdc passed all-status focused/exact duplicate checks."
body: "## Charter\nLiving capability epic for tracker self-governance: the checks and primitives that keep pm's own data trustworthy and machine-verifiable. Embodies the core philosophy — project management = context management — by guaranteeing an agent can rebuild full context from pm alone.\n\n## Scope\n- In: core/governance (content-fields, issue-codes, metadata-coverage), core/validate (fix-planning, estimate-defaults, missing-by-type, missing-link-owners, linked-artifact-reference, stale-file-classification), core/diagnostics/remediation registry, pm validate / pm health check surfaces, changelog governance (bucket-by-updated_at drag traps), and terminal-evidence backfill (resolution/close_reason).\n- Out: source-code quality gates — CodeFactor/ESLint/jscpd/LOC/CC (pm-92if); CLI command ergonomics themselves (pm-mpbb); schema/type customization (pm-8jdc).\n\n## Invariants this epic guards\n- Every pm validate / pm health warning must map to exactly one open remediation item (the 'no orphan warning' rule).\n- Review passes are CREATE-ONLY on closed items: touching a closed item updates updated_at and drags it into the current [Unreleased] changelog bucket. Backfills run in a dedicated tracker-only pass with same-commit changelog review.\n- No placeholder metadata: an honest empty beats fabricated 'done: done' resolution/close_reason evidence.\n- issue-code dedupe is title-prefix based; metadata-coverage predicates are shared primitives (core/governance/metadata-coverage) reused by validate + stats + aggregate.\n\n## Status\nContinues the closed governance epics pm-5rjn (continuous governance automation) and pm-wtsp (governance + docs overhaul); builds on pm-yq7m (coverage observability), pm-hm1q (metadata-coverage primitive), pm-6bz1 (validate accuracy), pm-dw5s (low-signal checks), pm-cc04 (remediation-registry ADR), pm-sz6w (machine-executable remediation). Opens as a living backlog per the capability-epic convention — new governance/validation/data-quality work lands here.\n\n## Open children (2026-07-04)\n- pm-e9zh — backfill terminal resolution + close_reason evidence without placeholders or changelog drag (validate: 268 resolution + 18 close_reason).\n- pm-j8z6 — reconcile linked-file ownership after source/test relocations (validate files: 146 missing + 134 orphaned paths).\n- pm-pivf — resolve duplicate issue-code GH-209 warning without changelog drag."
